.TH LPF-STATE 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.2.3" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-state \- inspect or modify conntrack state
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf state [\-\-json] <list|flush|kill>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Inspect and manage lpf\-related conntrack state.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-json
emit machine\-readable state output
.TP
\-\-src <addr>
source address for kill operation
.TP
\-\-dst <addr>
destination address for kill operation
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf state list \-\-json
lpf state kill \-\-src 10.0.0.1 \-\-dst 10.0.0.2
lpf state flush
.SH FILES
/proc/net/nf_conntrack
/var/lib/lpf/history
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Killing conntrack entries can interrupt active connections.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-rules(8), lpf\-history(8)
